TERMS AND CONDITIONS

1. Definition of Waqf
   A Waqf is a perpetual charitable endowment in Islamic law where a property is dedicated for a charitable purpose in perpetuity, and cannot be sold, inherited, or gifted.

2. Declaration of Waqf
   By applying this license to a work, the copyright holder dedicates any and all copyright interest in the work as a permanent charitable endowment (Waqf) for the benefit of humanity, seeking reward from Allah (سبحانه وتعالى).

